description: Expression levels of 77 proteins measured in the cerebral cortex of control and Down syndrome (trisomy) mice. Mice were exposed to context fear conditioning to assess associative learning, with some receiving memantine treatment.

creator.name: Clara Higuera
creator.affiliation: Department of Software Engineering and Artificial Intelligence, Faculty of Informatics, Complutense University, Madrid

creator.name: Katheleen J. Gardiner
creator.affiliation: Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology, Faculty of Chemistry, Complutense University, Madrid

creator.name: Krzysztof J. Cios
creator.affiliation: Department of Computer Science, Virginia Commonwealth University

feature_description: 77 protein expression levels measured in nuclear fraction of cortex. Each protein name is followed by '_n' indicating nuclear fraction measurement. Values represent expression levels detected through reverse phase protein array (RPPA).

target_values.c-CS-s: Control mice, stimulated to learn, saline injection (9 mice)
target_values.c-CS-m: Control mice, stimulated to learn, memantine injection (10 mice)
target_values.c-SC-s: Control mice, not stimulated to learn, saline injection (9 mice)
target_values.c-SC-m: Control mice, not stimulated to learn, memantine injection (10 mice)
target_values.t-CS-s: Trisomy mice, stimulated to learn, saline injection (7 mice)
target_values.t-CS-m: Trisomy mice, stimulated to learn, memantine injection (9 mice)
target_values.t-SC-s: Trisomy mice, not stimulated to learn, saline injection (9 mice)
target_values.t-SC-m: Trisomy mice, not stimulated to learn, memantine injection (9 mice)

use_case: Biomarker discovery for Down syndrome, understanding learning deficits, drug efficacy assessment, protein expression analysis in neurological disorders

learning_outcomes.trisomic_mice: Fail to learn unless treated with memantine

research_objectives: Identify protein subsets discriminant between classes, understand molecular basis of learning deficits in Down syndrome, evaluate memantine as potential treatment

data_characteristics.independence: Each measurement can be considered independent
data_characteristics.missing_data: Some technical artifacts resulted in missing values

advantages: Real biological data, important medical application, multiple experimental conditions, protein-level measurements
challenges: Missing values due to technical artifacts, relatively small sample size per class, complex interactions between proteins
biomedical_significance: First dataset to assess pharmacotherapy efficacy for Down syndrome cognitive deficits, potential for identifying therapeutic targets
ethical_considerations: Animal research conducted under appropriate protocols, aimed at understanding and treating human genetic disorder

citations.author: Clara Higuera, Katheleen J. Gardiner, and Krzysztof J. Cios
citations.title: Self-Organizing Feature Maps Identify Proteins Critical to Learning in a Mouse Model of Down Syndrome

citations.author: Md Mahmudulla Hassan Ahmed et al.
citations.title: Protein dynamics associated with failed and rescued learning in the Ts65Dn mouse model of Down syndrome
